5000|$|Betty Boyd {{was born}} in 1924 in Tulsa, Oklahoma to Ted and Marie (Fairchild) Carman. Boyd was raised by her mother, grandmother, and several maiden aunts. Her {{interest}} in reading and writing began early in life. When asked about her interests, Boyd said [...] "I wanted to write. I knew that. I loved journalism when I got to that point in school. In junior high, we had a junior high school paper {{at that time and}} I loved writing for that, that kind of <b>writing,not</b> books although I’ve done that some since.” She graduated from Tulsa Central High School where she served as the yearbook editor.|$|E

